# [[philter]] {{gloss|a kind of potion, charm, or drug intended to make the drinker fall in love with the giver}}
#* {{quote-book
|fr
|year=1857
|author=w:Charles Baudelaire
|title=Les Fleurs du mal
|chapter=L'Irréparable
|chapterurl={{fullurl:s:fr:Les_Fleurs_du_mal/1857/L’Irréparable}}
|passage=Dans quel '''philtre''', dans quel vin, dans quelle tisane, / Noierons-nous ce vieil ennemi, / Destructeur et gourmand comme la courtisane, / Patient comme la fourmi?
|translator=John Collings Squire
|translation=What wine, what drug, what '''philtre''' known of man / Will drown this ancient foe, / Ruthless and ravenous as a courtesan, / Sure as an ant, and slow?}}
